Strengths

Pick strengths that matter for a 5+ year backend developer:

Example Answer

One of my strengths is taking ownership of features. Once a requirement is assigned to me, I make sure to understand it clearly and deliver a complete and reliable implementation.

Another strength is writing clean and maintainable code. I pay attention to things like code structure, readability, and performance, especially in backend services.

I also value team collaboration, and I actively participate in code reviews and discussions to improve the overall quality of the codebase.

Weakness

Choose a safe weakness that doesn't hurt your role.

Example Answer

One area I’m working on is sometimes spending extra time exploring different technical solutions before deciding on one. I like to understand problems deeply, but occasionally this can take more time.

To improve this, I now try to discuss approaches earlier with teammates so we can reach a decision faster.

Short Version (Very Good in Interviews)

If they want a quick answer:

My strengths are taking ownership of tasks, writing clean and maintainable backend code, and collaborating well with teammates during code reviews and feature discussions.

One area I’m improving is sometimes spending extra time exploring solutions independently, so I’m working on discussing approaches earlier with the team to make decisions faster.

Why This Works

This answer shows:

✅ Ownership
✅ Code quality
✅ Teamwork
✅ Self-improvement mindset

All are traits hiring managers want in senior developers.

💡 Small interview trick:
After saying your strength, give a small example:

For example, in my current project I handled the Razorpay payment integration and ensured proper webhook verification and error handling.

This makes your answer much stronger and more believable.

